We replace the complex decomposition of `f` and the subsequent `calc` block with a simpler one. The new `calc` block will directly use `f` and its real and imaginary parts.

The line of thought is to express `f` in terms of its real and imaginary parts multiplied by coefficients in `{1, -1, RCLike.I, -RCLike.I}`. This is done using `simp` and `ring_nf`.

